RULES OF CONDUCT

AetherMUD is a small hobby MUD. These rules keep the game fun for everyone.

1. Be respectful. Harassment, slurs, and targeted abuse are not tolerated.
2. Stay in character in the game world. Use OOC for out-of-character chat.
3. No cheating: multi-playing to gain unfair advantage, exploiting bugs,
   or using bots to automate gameplay without staff approval.
4. Do not share account passwords. You are responsible for your character.
5. Follow staff directions. Wizards may intervene in disputes or remove
   disruptive players.
6. Report problems with bug, idea, or typo commands, or contact staff on OOC.

Violations may result in warnings, temporary bans, or permanent removal
depending on severity. See help three strikes, harassment, and reporting.

SEE ALSO: roleplaying, consent, harassment, reporting, faq
